NCID distributions:

    sourceforge:
        NCID Source package:           ncid-0.76-src.tar.gz

        Cygwin 32 bit Windows package: ncid-0.76-1-cygwin.tgz

        TiVo Series1 package:          ncid-0.76-1-ppc-tivo.tgz
        TiVo Series 2 and 3 package:   ncid-0.76-1-mips-tivo.tgz

        Ubuntu 32 bit packages:        ncid_0.76-0ubuntu1_i386.deb
                                       ncid-client_0.76-0ubuntu1_all.deb
                                       ncid-kpopup_0.76-0ubuntu1_all.deb
                                       ncid-mythtv_0.76-0ubuntu1_all.deb
                                       ncid-samba_0.76-0ubuntu1_all.deb
                                       ncid-speak_0.76-0ubuntu1_all.deb

        Windows client installer:      ncid-0.76-1-client_setup.exe

    Fedora packages:
        # available at the Fedora repository
        # there is a server, client, and optional output module packages
        # normally you only need to install the ncid & ncid-client rpm packages
        # The yum list command will show you the packages available
        yum list ncid\*

    Macintosh OS X package:
        # available at MacPorts
        http://trac.macports.org/browser/trunk/dports/net/ncid/Portfile

    FreeBSD package:
        # available at FreshPorts
        http://www.freshports.org/comms/ncid/

Specific distribution Changes:

    Fedora and Redhat:

        NOTES:
            If you need to build packages for your specific OS release:
                rpmbuild -tb ncid-0.76-src.tar.gz

    FreeBSD:

    Mac OS-X:

    Ubuntu:

        NOTES:
            If you need to build a package for your specific OS release, the
            build-essential, fakeroot, & libpcap packages must be installed:
                sudo apt-get build-essential fakeroot libpcap0.8-dev
                tar -xzf ncid-0.76-src.tar.gz
                mv ncid ncid-0.76
                cd ncid-0.76
                fakeroot debian/rules build
                fakeroot debian/rules binary
                fakeroot debian/rules clean

    TiVo:
        Fixed the ncid client terminating because of no utf-8 encoding.

    Windows:

NCID Server Changes:

    ncidd:
        Added seconds to date and time in debug and log file

NCID Gateway Changes:

    sip2ncid:
        Added seconds to date and time in debug and log file

        Added time to the no SIP packets warning message

        Fixed Warning message and eliminated multiple messages on
        same call for Babytel in Montreal

    ncidsip:
        Fixed Warning message and eliminated multiple messages on
        same call for Babytel in Montreal

    yac2ncid:

NCID Client Changes:

    ncid:
        Modified the ncid client so a failure to set utf-8 encoding
        would not result in the program terminating.

        Added option to disable the "close Window" button.  With this
        option enabled, the menu item File/Quit must be used to terminate
        the program.

NCID Client Module Changes:

Documentation Changes:
        Updated ncid.1, Setup-ncidsip, and Setup-sip2ncid
        Corrected spelling errors in the INSTALL* files

